courses.customDesc: One course from each of the following GE areas must be completed: A1, A2, A3, B1, B3, (B4 [lab] must be completed with B3), B1-B5 elective, C1, C2, C3, C4, D1, D2, D4, D5, and F. C4, D5, and F should be taken only after Junior standing is reached (90 units). One (1) course must be completed from B1, in addition to STAT 217. No ANT/GEOG class may be taken to fulfill GE D5. Refer to online catalog for GE course selection, United States Cultural Pluralism (USCP) and Graduation Writing Requirement (GWR). USCP requirement can be satisfied by some (but not all) courses within GE categories: C3, C4, D1, D4, D5 or F.

One course from each of the following GE areas must be completed: A1, A2, A3, B1, Upper-Division B, C1, C2, Lower-Division C Elective, Upper-Division C, D1, E, and GE Elective. Upper-Division B & Upper-Division C should be taken only after junior standing is reached (90 units).
The following courses can go here: GEOG300, GEOG340, GEOG370, GEOG380

When creating an individual program, it should consist of 28 units, with 16 of the 28 at the 300-400 level. Courses are selected by the student in consultation with an advising faculty member. The student must also provide a written justification for the courses and the way they constitute a cohesive, integrated course of study. The list of courses is a contract between the student and the Department.

If GE courses are taken for a letter grade and used as concentration electives, additional free electives may be required to complete the 180 total degree requirement. See College Advisor for additional information.
